Binary search in java using Arrays.binarySearch() method

We can also execute binary search using Arrays.binarySearch() method in java. Here's an example

import java.util.Arrays;
public class UsingArraysBinarySearch
{
   public static void main(String[] args)
   {
      int[] arrNumbers = {15,16,17,18,19};
      int keyElement = 17;
      int output = Arrays.binarySearch(arrNumbers, keyElement);
      if(output < 0)
      {
         System.out.println("Element not found!");
      }
      else
      {
         System.out.println("Element found at index: " + output);
      }
   }
}

Output:

Element found at index: 2

